data.description: GREAT HOUSE FOR SALE!! Zoned RR5 and dividable! Luxury homes? Boutique Vineyard? Christmas tree farm? Possibilities abound! 7 minutes to Scappoose Airport. Here is an enchanting property including a mesmerizing view in Columbia County OR. Be wowed by the natural beauty and opportunities. Buyer's due diligence. Zoned RR-5 so purchaser has options! One can develop to the max permissible, or leave it like it is and choose a prime home site for a forever dream home. The gently sloping hillside affords excellent building sites! The view is to the east all the way across the valley to an outstanding view of the majestic peaks of the Cascades. The fields could remain grass hay, homes, tree farm, vineyard and there is approximately 4 acres of marketable timber... brilliant! You choose! The privacy of this setting is unbeatable---quiet, tranquil and a perpetual feast for the eyes.This dwelling is a charmingly restored 1920's farmhouse with a cook's kitchen featuring high end gas range and side by side double capacity refrigerator and freezer, knotty pine vaulted vaulted living room, and two baths, one with soak tub, designer blinds in most rooms. Just minutes to downtown Scappoose and a short twenty minutes from there to NW Portland. A wonderfully clear artesian well supplies abundant water. House and well are wired for generator. Architectural hardscape and landscape grace the steps to the garage. There is a gated driveway, fenced lower pasture, garden, fruit trees and chicken coop. Come see this magical setting. Additional information available on request.
